 ADR-001: Single Containerized Service ArchitectureAll functional components will be bundled into a single Docker image 
and deployed as one container. Service discovery, routing, and inter‑component communication will occur via in‑process c
alls or lightweight messaging within the same process.### ADR-002: HTTPS‑Only Public EndpointsAll API and redirect endpo
ints will be exposed over HTTPS only. The application will terminate TLS at the service boundary and issue a 301/302 red
irect for any incoming HTTP request.### ADR-003: PostgreSQL 16+ as Primary Persistence LayerAll components that persist 
data will use the same Postgres 16 database instance. Connection pooling via PgBouncer will be employed to manage connec
tions efficiently.### ADR-005: Structured JSON Logging to StdoutAll components will use a common logging framework (e.g.
, Logback with JSON encoder) that writes structured JSON records to stdout. Logs will include fields such as timestamp, 
level, component, request_id, and message.### ADR-010: Structured JSON Error ResponsesAll services will return errors in
 the format `{ "error": { "code": "<CODE>", "message": "<USER_FRIENDLY_MESSAGE>" } }` with appropriate HTTP status codes
. The error code set is defined centrally and referenced by all components.## Refactoring Idempotency Constraint(not app
