[38;5;15m}[m
[37m```[m

[37m---[m

[34m### Step 2: Wire Into Existing Short-Link Creation Handler  [m
[33m[1m**Action:**[37m[22m Hook into the existing POST [32m`/create-link` [37mor similar endpoint and call my initializer [33m[1m**inside its transact[m
[33m[1m[39;120Htion block**[37m[22m:[K[m
[37m- If using connection pools from [32m`@shared/lib/db`[37m, inject a new pool instance via DI/config.[K[m
[37m- Run initialization immediately after link insertion but before returning success response to client (to avoid 429 rate[m
[37m[39;120He limit errors).[m

[37m---[m

[34m### Step 3: Execute Database Write With Transaction Safety[2C[m
[33m[1m**Action:**[37m[22m In Node.js native or Express style code, execute:[K[2C[m

[37m```[38;5;9mjavascript[K[m
[37mdbPool.execute([m
[37m    [35m`[32mUPDATE links SET click_count = COALESCE(click_count, 0)::int[K[1C[m
[32m     WHERE mapping_id = $1[35m`[37m,[K[m
[37m    [linkId][m
[37m); [38;5;8m// or INSERT INTO mappings IF NOT EXISTS with default=counter=0[K[m
[37m```[m

[37mFor PostgreSQL unique constraint handling (as per user note in Mapping.ts), ensure initializer only runs once-per-link a[m
[37m[39;120Hand handles race conditions via [32m`ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING` [37mclause as fallback.[K[m

[37m---[m

